# S3 AccessDenied Troubleshooting Lab

## Objective
Simulated and resolved AWS S3 AccessDenied errors using IAM policies and AWS CLI.

## Services Used
- Amazon S3
- AWS IAM
- AWS CLI

## Problem
IAM user could not upload files to S3 bucket due to missing permissions.

## Root Cause
The IAM user did not have required S3 access policies attached.

## Troubleshooting Steps
1. Configured AWS CLI
2. Attempted S3 upload
3. Observed AccessDenied error
4. Checked IAM permissions
5. Attached AmazonS3FullAccess policy
6. Verified successful upload

## Resolution
Successfully uploaded files to S3 after fixing IAM permissions.

## Skills Learned
- IAM troubleshooting
- AWS CLI
- S3 permissions
- Cloud debugging
